During 2010, tax unit boundary information was gathered from Kansas County Clerks by DASC and resulted in the first statewide GIS tax unit boundary data file. Certifications are on-going and are integrated as they are received. Users will want to download this data frequently for updates.</abstract>       <purpose>To create a statewide GIS tax unit boundary data file.</purpose>     </descript>     <timeperd>       <timeinfo>         <sngdate>           <caldate>20111130</caldate>         </sngdate>       </timeinfo>       <current>publication date</current>     </timeperd>     <status>       <progress>In work</progress>       <update>As needed</update>     </status>     <spdom>       <bounding>         <westbc>-102.172161</westbc>         <eastbc>-94.434024</eastbc>         <northbc>40.058715</northbc>         <southbc>36.918533</southbc>       </bounding>     </spdom>     <keywords>       <theme>         <themekt>None</themekt>         <themekey>tax units</themekey>         <themekey>Kansas County Clerks</themekey>         <themekey>tax unit boundaries</themekey>         <themekey>assessments</themekey>       </theme>       <theme>         <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Categories</themekt>         <themekey>boundaries</themekey>       </theme>     </keywords>     <accconst>None</accconst>     <useconst>The State of Kansas Geographic Information Systems Core Database's digital data have been tested and their documentation carefully reviewed.
